---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Cortex — Red Team Kitchen"
  description="Cortex is a Nous Research x Kimi Hackathon brain-viewer project: TRIBE v2 predictions, Gemma narration, and durable gallery recordings from the local RTX 5090 stack."
>
  <article class="wrap">
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="pills">
        <span class="pill brand">Project · Cortex</span>
        <span class="pill gold">Nous Research × Kimi Hackathon</span>
        <span class="pill">Local app · PC required</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Brain-response media, <em>made visible.</em></h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Cortex turns submitted media into a TRIBE v2 cortical-response prediction, a
        3D/ASCII brain visualization, and four parallel narrations. The first viewer
        was built during the Nous Research × Kimi sprint; the work later pointed us
        toward deeper MRI and fMRI research questions that deserve a slower, more
        rigorous follow-up.
      </p>
      <div class="ctas">
        <a class="cta primary" href="https://github.com/AlexiosBluffMara/cortex">Cortex GitHub</a>
        <a class="cta" href="https://cortex.redteamkitchen.com/gallery.html">Live gallery when online</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="status">
      <h2>Current Status</h2>
      <p>
        Cortex is running locally again on Seratonin, the RTX 5090 desktop, at
        <code>http://127.0.0.1:8765</code>. The Cloudflare Tunnel route can expose it
        at <code>cortex.redteamkitchen.com</code>, but that route only works while the
        PC, the watchdog, and the tunnel are all healthy. The old Tailscale Funnel
        URLs are retired and should not be used in public copy.
      </p>
      <p>
        The durable public path is to publish selected recordings, generated
        brain-response clips, thumbnails, and scan metadata from Cloudflare Pages/R2,
        then treat the live app as an optional lab mode rather than the primary demo.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Gallery Artifacts</h2>
      <div class="media-grid">
        <article class="media-card">
          <video controls preload="metadata" src="/media/cortex/cortex_gallery_captioned.mp4"></video>
          <div>
            <p class="tag">Gallery recording</p>
            <h3>Completed scans, narrations, and regions</h3>
            <p>
              A captioned recording of the local gallery surface. This is the kind of
              asset we can serve reliably from Cloudflare without keeping the 5090
              app public every minute of the day.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="media-card">
          <video controls loop muted preload="metadata" src="/media/cortex/artemis_launch_brain_ascii.mp4"></video>
          <div>
            <p class="tag">TRIBE output</p>
            <h3>Artemis launch brain-response clip</h3>
            <p>
              A generated BOLD-response video from a completed Cortex scan. These
              artifacts are small, portable, and ideal for the public gallery.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>What It Proved</h2>
      <div class="panel">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Working local pipeline:</strong> the FastAPI app, TRIBE v2 outputs, generated brain videos, and scan registry all work on the local RTX 5090 machine.</li>
          <li><strong>Public strategy change:</strong> dynamic uploads should not be the default public promise; static artifacts should carry the website.</li>
          <li><strong>Research direction:</strong> the project is a prototype for media-to-brain-response exploration, not a diagnostic tool or a substitute for clinical fMRI.</li>
          <li><strong>Source:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/AlexiosBluffMara/cortex">github.com/AlexiosBluffMara/cortex</a>.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero { padding-top: var(--rtk-sp-7); }
  .pills { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--rtk-sp-2); margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-4); }
  .pill {
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: var(--rtk-radius-pill);
    border: 1px solid var(--rtk-border-strong);
    font-family: var(--rtk-font-mono);
    font-size: var(--rtk-fs-xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--rtk-text-muted);
  }
  .pill.brand { color: var(--rtk-cardinal-bright); border-color: var(--rtk-cardinal); }
  .pill.gold  { color: var(--rtk-isu-gold-bright); border-color: var(--rtk-isu-gold); }

  h1 { font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw + 1rem, 4rem); margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-5); }
  h1 em { color: var(--rtk-cardinal-bright); font-style: italic; }
  .lede { color: var(--rtk-text-muted); max-width: 66ch; font-size: var(--rtk-fs-md); margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-6); }

  .ctas { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--rtk-sp-3); margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-8); }
  .cta {
    padding: var(--rtk-sp-3) var(--rtk-sp-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--rtk-border-strong);
    border-radius: var(--rtk-radius-pill);
    color: var(--rtk-text);
    font-size: var(--rtk-fs-sm);
  }
  .cta:hover { background: var(--rtk-surface-2); }
  .cta.primary { background: var(--rtk-cardinal); border-color: var(--rtk-cardinal); color: #fff; }
  .cta.primary:hover { background: var(--rtk-cardinal-bright); }

  section { margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-8); }
  .status {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--rtk-isu-gold);
    background: var(--rtk-surface-1);
    padding: var(--rtk-sp-5);
    border-radius: 0 var(--rtk-radius-sm) var(--rtk-radius-sm) 0;
  }
  .status p,
  .panel li,
  .media-card p { color: var(--rtk-text-muted); }

  code {
    background: var(--rtk-surface-2);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: var(--rtk-radius-sm);
    color: var(--rtk-isu-gold);
  }

  .media-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--rtk-sp-5);
  }
  .media-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--rtk-border);
    background: var(--rtk-surface-1);
    border-radius: var(--rtk-radius-sm);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .media-card video {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
    display: block;
    background: #000;
  }
  .media-card div { padding: var(--rtk-sp-5); }
  .media-card .tag {
    margin: 0 0 var(--rtk-sp-2);
    color: var(--rtk-isu-gold);
    font-family: var(--rtk-font-mono);
    font-size: var(--rtk-fs-xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .media-card h3 { margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-2); }

  .panel {
    border: 1px solid var(--rtk-border);
    background: var(--rtk-surface-1);
    border-radius: var(--rtk-radius-sm);
    padding: var(--rtk-sp-5);
  }
  .panel ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; }
  .panel li { margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-3); }
  .panel strong { color: var(--rtk-text); }
</style>
